  "prompt": "Why is my code not working?",
  "response": "To help you effectively, I'll need to see the code you're working with and understand what specific issues or errors you are encountering. Please provide your code snippet along with any error messages or a description of the problem you're facing.\n\nHere are some general steps you can follow to diagnose issues:\n\n1. **Check for Syntax Errors**: Ensure that your code has no typos or missing characters. Most programming languages will display an error message if there's a syntax problem.\n\n2. **Debugging Output**: Insert print statements or use a debugger to track the values of variables and the flow of your program. This can help you identify where things are going wrong.\n\n3. **Consult Documentation**: Ensure that you are using functions and libraries correctly by referring to official documentation.\n\n4. **Check for Edge Cases**: Consider if your code is failing under certain conditions or input values.\n\n5. **Isolation of Code Segments**: Try isolating different parts of your code to pinpoint the issue. Run smaller sections independently to confirm they work as expected.\n\nPlease share the relevant details, and I'll do my best to help you debug the problem.",
